    <stitle>ALTERNATOR: DELCO-REMY 27-SI SERIES, TYPE 200 - REPAIR PROCEDURES - BEARING REPLACEMENT AND LUBRICATION
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="replace" graphiccount="2">
        <title>BEARING REPLACEMENT AND LUBRICATION</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0801514">Figure 14</hotlnk>for all Item number callouts in parentheses.
            </para>
            <figure id="f0801514" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0801514" filename="../figg08/G0801514.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Exploded View of 27-SI Alternator</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. SLIP RING END FRAME</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. REGULATOR</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. BRUSH HOLDER</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. ROTOR</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. STATOR</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. NUT</callout1>
                    <callout1>7. WAVE WASHER</callout1>
                    <callout1>8. PULLEY</callout1>
                    <callout1>9. FAN</callout1>
                    <callout1>10. COLLAR (OUTER)</callout1>
                    <callout1>11. DRIVE END FRAME</callout1>
                    <callout1>12. GASKET</callout1>
                    <callout1>13. BEARING</callout1>
                    <callout1>14. COLLAR (INNER)</callout1>
                    <callout1>15. RETAINER PLATE</callout1>
                    <callout1>16. BEARING</callout1>
                    <callout1>17. SEAL</callout1>
                    <callout1>18. THROUGH-BOLT</callout1>
                    <callout1>19. DIODE TRIO</callout1>
                    <callout1>20. RECTIFIER BRIDGE</callout1>
                    <callout1>21. CAPACITOR</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>To Replace The Drive End Bearing:</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove shaft nut (Item 6) , pulley (Item 8), fan (Item 9) and outer collar (Item 10).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Press rotor (Item 4) from drive end frame (Item 11).</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove retainer plate screws, retainer plate assembly (Item 15), gasket (Item 12) and
                    collar (Item 13).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Press bearing (Item 13) from drive end frame (Item 12).</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Press bearing (Item 13) into drive end frame (Item 12).</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Attach gasket (Item 12) and retainer plate (Item 15) to drive end frame.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With collar (Item 14) on rotor shaft, press rotor (Item 4) into drive end frame bearing
                    (Item 13).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Assemble collar (Item 10), fan (Item 9), pulley (Item 8) and nut (Item 6). Tighten nut
                    to 70 to 80 ft-lbs. (95 to 108 N&#8226;m). To assist in tightening the drive pulley nut a hexagon
                    hole is provided in the end of the rotor shaft for holding with an Allen wrench.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <para>The bearing in the slip ring end frame should be replaced if its grease supply is exhausted. No
                attempt should be made to relubricate and reuse the bearing. To remove the bearing from the slip ring
                end frame, press out with a tube or collar that just fits inside the end frame housing. Press from the
                outside of the housing towards the inside.
            </para>
            <para>
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0801515">Figure 15</hotlnk>shows installation of the prelubricated, sealed type
                bearing. Use a length of thin wall tube in the space between grease cup and housing (Item A,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0801515">Figure 15</hotlnk>) to push bearing in until end of grease cup is flush with
                housing.
            </para>
            <figure id="f0801515" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0801515" filename="../figg08/G0801515.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Installation of Prelubricated Skip Ring End Bearing</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>A. SPACE</callout1>
                    <callout1>1. RECTIFIER END FRAME</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. BEARING (PRELUBRICATED)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcsubproc>
